definition.value: An L-talopyranose that has alpha- configuration at the anomeric centre.
An amino disaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose and 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
An L-threo-hex-4-enopyranuronosyl-(1->4)-D-GlcpNS in which both anomeric centres have beta configuration.
A trisaccharide consisting of D-galactopyranose, beta-D-galactopyranose and D-glucopyranose joined in sequence by (1->6) and (1->4) glycosidic bonds.

A linear amino tetrasaccharide comprising alpha-D-galactosyl, beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residues linked sequentially (1->3), (1->4) and (1->6).
A trisaccharide that is alpha-L-fucopyranose in which the hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 3 have each been converted into the corresponding beta-D-galactopyranosyl derivative.
